==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: ô'tŏp"sē
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈɔːˌtɒpsiː/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"O:%tQpsi:/

===Noun===
'''autopsy''' (plural: [[autopsies]])

# A dissection performed on a [[cadaver]] to find possible cause(s) of death.
# Carry out a personal inspection; to see for one's self.

====Synonyms====
*[[necropsy]]
*[[post-mortem]]
====Usage note====
* The term [[necropsy]] is usually used for animals, with [[autopsy]] reserved for human beings.

